When the API is called the "problemStatus" will be checked, if it is "started" then the "problemID" and "problemSeverity" will\
be added to a list and and based on the "problemSeverity" a LED and/or buzzer will be turned ON,\
if the "problemStatus" is "updated" then the "problemID will be looked up in the list and the "problemSeverity" should be updated,\
if the "problemStatus" is "resolved" then the "problemID will be looked up in the list and removed, \
after a "updated" or "resolved" event the list will be checked again and compared to the currently ON LEDs, if a cooresponding LED does not have an active\
problem it should be turned OFF, if all problems are resolved then all LED's and the buzzer should be turned OFF and the Green LED should be turned ON.\
\
